\begin_layout Subsection
Sovereign Risk
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The UIP does not take into account the 
\series bold
default risk
\series default
 (of each country, compared to another one).
 which arises form the instruments being issued by different parties.
 It differentiates the different assets.
 Denoting the default risk premium at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $CRP(t)$
\end_inset

 we can write the UIP equation as:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
i(NIS)=i(\$)+\left[\frac{E_{t}[S_{t+1}-S_{t}]}{S_{t}}\right]+CRP_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
